  <Name>k__BackingField: Colossians
  fancyName: 
  nickname: col
  language: English
  lang: eng
  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: 'This letter is from Paul, chosen by the will of God to be an apostle
        of Christ Jesus, and from our brother Timothy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We are writing to God\u2019s holy people in the city of Colosse,
        who are faithful brothers and sisters[COMMENT[0]] in Christ.\n\tMay God our
        Father give you grace and peace.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: faithful brothers.
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Thanksgiving and Prayer"
      content: 'We always pray for you, and we give thanks to God, the Father of
        our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For we have heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and your love for
        all of God\u2019s people, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'which come from your confident hope of what God has reserved for
        you in heaven. You have had this expectation ever since you first heard the
        truth of the Good News.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This same Good News that came to you is going out all over the world.
        It is bearing fruit everywhere by changing lives, just as it changed your
        lives from the day you first heard and understood the truth about God\u2019s
        wonderful grace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You learned about the Good News from Epaphras, our beloved co-worker.
        He is Christ\u2019s faithful servant, and he is helping us on your behalf.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'he is ministering on your behalf; '
        - ft: 'some manuscripts read '
          body: he is ministering on our behalf.
    - title: 
      content: 'He has told us about the love for others that the Holy Spirit has
        given you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we have not stopped praying for you since we first heard about
        you. We ask God to give you complete knowledge of his will and to give you
        spiritual wisdom and understanding. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the way you live will always honor and please the Lord, and
        your lives will produce every kind of good fruit. All the while, you will
        grow as you learn to know God better and better.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We also pray that you will be strengthened with all his glorious
        power so you will have all the endurance and patience you need. May you be
        filled with joy,[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: all the patience and endurance you need with joy.
    - title: 
      content: 'always thanking the Father. He has enabled you to share in the inheritance
        that belongs to his people, who live in the light. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he has rescued us from the kingdom of darkness and transferred
        us into the Kingdom of his dear Son, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'who purchased our freedom[COMMENT[0]] and forgave our sins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts add '
          body: with his blood.
    - title: Christ Is Supreme
      content: "Christ is the visible image of the invisible God.\n\tHe existed before
        anything was created and is supreme over all creation,[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: He is the firstborn of all creation.
    - title: 
      content: "for through him God created everything\n\tin the heavenly realms
        and on earth.\n\tHe made the things we can see\n\tand the things we can\u2019t
        see\u2014\n\tsuch as thrones, kingdoms, rulers, and authorities in the unseen
        world.\n\tEverything was created through him and for him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He existed before anything else,\n\tand he holds all creation together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Christ is also the head of the church,\n\twhich is his body.\n\tHe
        is the beginning,\n\tsupreme over all who rise from the dead.[COMMENT[0]]So
        he is first in everything.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the firstborn from the dead.
    - title: 
      content: "For God in all his fullness\n\twas pleased to live in Christ,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and through him God reconciled\n\teverything to himself.\n\tHe made
        peace with everything in heaven and on earth\n\tby means of Christ\u2019s
        blood on the cross.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This includes you who were once far away from God. You were his enemies,
        separated from him by your evil thoughts and actions. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet now he has reconciled you to himself through the death of Christ
        in his physical body. As a result, he has brought you into his own presence,
        and you are holy and blameless as you stand before him without a single fault.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you must continue to believe this truth and stand firmly in it.
        Don\u2019t drift away from the assurance you received when you heard the
        Good News. The Good News has been preached all over the world, and I, Paul,
        have been appointed as God\u2019s servant to proclaim it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Work for the Church"
      content: 'I am glad when I suffer for you in my body, for I am participating
        in the sufferings of Christ that continue for his body, the church. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has given me the responsibility of serving his church by proclaiming
        his entire message to you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This message was kept secret for centuries and generations past,
        but now it has been revealed to God\u2019s people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God wanted them to know that the riches and glory of Christ are
        for you Gentiles, too. And this is the secret: Christ lives in you. This
        gives you assurance of sharing his glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we tell others about Christ, warning everyone and teaching everyone
        with all the wisdom God has given us. We want to present them to God, perfect[COMMENT[0]]
        in their relationship to Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:28 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: mature.
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s why I work and struggle so hard, depending on Christ\u2019s
        mighty power that works within me."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'I want you to know how much I have agonized for you and for the church
        at Laodicea, and for many other believers who have never met me personally. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I want them to be encouraged and knit together by strong ties of
        love. I want them to have complete confidence that they understand God\u2019s
        mysterious plan, which is Christ himself. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In him lie hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am telling you this so no one will deceive you with well-crafted
        arguments. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For though I am far away from you, my heart is with you. And I rejoice
        that you are living as you should and that your faith in Christ is strong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Freedom from Rules and New Life in Christ
      content: 'And now, just as you accepted Christ Jesus as your Lord, you must
        continue to follow him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let your roots grow down into him, and let your lives be built on
        him. Then your faith will grow strong in the truth you were taught, and you
        will overflow with thankfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let anyone capture you with empty philosophies and high-sounding
        nonsense that come from human thinking and from the spiritual powers[COMMENT[0]]
        of this world, rather than from Christ. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'the spiritual principles; '
        - ft: also in 2:20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'For in Christ lives all the fullness of God in a human body.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: in him dwells all the completeness of the Godhead bodily.
    - title: 
      content: 'So you also are complete through your union with Christ, who is the
        head over every ruler and authority.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you came to Christ, you were \u201Ccircumcised,\u201D but not
        by a physical procedure. Christ performed a spiritual circumcision\u2014the
        cutting away of your sinful nature.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the cutting away of the body of the flesh.
    - title: 
      content: 'For you were buried with Christ when you were baptized. And with
        him you were raised to new life because you trusted the mighty power of God,
        who raised Christ from the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You were dead because of your sins and because your sinful nature
        was not yet cut away. Then God made you alive with Christ, for he forgave
        all our sins. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He canceled the record of the charges against us and took it away
        by nailing it to the cross. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In this way, he disarmed[COMMENT[0]] the spiritual rulers and authorities.
        He shamed them publicly by his victory over them on the cross.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: he stripped off.
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t let anyone condemn you for what you eat or drink, or
        for not celebrating certain holy days or new moon ceremonies or Sabbaths. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For these rules are only shadows of the reality yet to come. And
        Christ himself is that reality. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let anyone condemn you by insisting on pious self-denial
        or the worship of angels,[COMMENT[0]] saying they have had visions about
        these things. Their sinful minds have made them proud, "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: or worshiping with angels.
    - title: 
      content: 'and they are not connected to Christ, the head of the body. For he
        holds the whole body together with its joints and ligaments, and it grows
        as God nourishes it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have died with Christ, and he has set you free from the spiritual
        powers of this world. So why do you keep on following the rules of the world,
        such as, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t handle! Don\u2019t taste! Don\u2019t touch!\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such rules are mere human teachings about things that deteriorate
        as we use them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These rules may seem wise because they require strong devotion, pious
        self-denial, and severe bodily discipline. But they provide no help in conquering
        a person\u2019s evil desires."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Living the New Life
      content: "Since you have been raised to new life with Christ, set your sights
        on the realities of heaven, where Christ sits in the place of honor at God\u2019s
        right hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Think about the things of heaven, not the things of earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you died to this life, and your real life is hidden with Christ
        in God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when Christ, who is your[COMMENT[0]] life, is revealed to the
        whole world, you will share in all his glory.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: our.
    - title: 
      content: "So put to death the sinful, earthly things lurking within you. Have
        nothing to do with sexual immorality, impurity, lust, and evil desires. Don\u2019t
        be greedy, for a greedy person is an idolater, worshiping the things of this
        world. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of these sins, the anger of God is coming.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: is coming on all who disobey him.
    - title: 
      content: 'You used to do these things when your life was still part of this
        world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now is the time to get rid of anger, rage, malicious behavior,
        slander, and dirty language. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t lie to each other, for you have stripped off your old
        sinful nature and all its wicked deeds. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Put on your new nature, and be renewed as you learn to know your
        Creator and become like him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In this new life, it doesn\u2019t matter if you are a Jew or a Gentile,[COMMENT[0]]
        circumcised or uncircumcised, barbaric, uncivilized,[COMMENT[1]] slave, or
        free. Christ is all that matters, and he lives in all of us.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:11a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: a Greek.
      - number: '3:11b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: Barbarian, Scythian.
    - title: 
      content: 'Since God chose you to be the holy people he loves, you must clothe
        yourselves with tenderhearted mercy, kindness, humility, gentleness, and
        patience. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Make allowance for each other\u2019s faults, and forgive anyone who
        offends you. Remember, the Lord forgave you, so you must forgive others. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Above all, clothe yourselves with love, which binds us all together
        in perfect harmony. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And let the peace that comes from Christ rule in your hearts. For
        as members of one body you are called to live in peace. And always be thankful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the message about Christ, in all its richness, fill your lives.
        Teach and counsel each other with all the wisdom he gives. Sing psalms and
        hymns and spiritual songs to God with thankful hearts. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And whatever you do or say, do it as a representative of the Lord
        Jesus, giving thanks through him to God the Father.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Instructions for Christian Households
      content: 'Wives, submit to your husbands, as is fitting for those who belong
        to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Husbands, love your wives and never treat them harshly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Children, always obey your parents, for this pleases the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fathers, do not aggravate your children, or they will become discouraged.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Slaves, obey your earthly masters in everything you do. Try to please
        them all the time, not just when they are watching you. Serve them sincerely
        because of your reverent fear of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Work willingly at whatever you do, as though you were working for
        the Lord rather than for people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember that the Lord will give you an inheritance as your reward,
        and that the Master you are serving is Christ.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: and serve Christ as your Master.
    - title: 
      content: But if you do what is wrong, you will be paid back for the wrong you
        have done. For God has no favorites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Masters, be just and fair to your slaves. Remember that you also
        have a Master\u2014in heaven.  "
      comments: []
    - title: An Encouragement for Prayer
      content: 'Devote yourselves to prayer with an alert mind and a thankful heart. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pray for us, too, that God will give us many opportunities to speak
        about his mysterious plan concerning Christ. That is why I am here in chains. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pray that I will proclaim this message as clearly as I should.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Live wisely among those who are not believers, and make the most
        of every opportunity. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let your conversation be gracious and attractive[COMMENT[0]] so that
        you will have the right response for everyone.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: and seasoned with salt.
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Instructions and Greetings"
      content: "Tychicus will give you a full report about how I am getting along.
        He is a beloved brother and faithful helper who serves with me in the Lord\u2019s
        work. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have sent him to you for this very purpose\u2014to let you know
        how we are doing and to encourage you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am also sending Onesimus, a faithful and beloved brother, one of
        your own people. He and Tychicus will tell you everything that\u2019s happening
        here.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Aristarchus, who is in prison with me, sends you his greetings, and
        so does Mark, Barnabas\u2019s cousin. As you were instructed before, make
        Mark welcome if he comes your way. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jesus (the one we call Justus) also sends his greetings. These are
        the only Jewish believers among my co-workers; they are working with me here
        for the Kingdom of God. And what a comfort they have been!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Epaphras, a member of your own fellowship and a servant of Christ
        Jesus, sends you his greetings. He always prays earnestly for you, asking
        God to make you strong and perfect, fully confident that you are following
        the whole will of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I can assure you that he prays hard for you and also for the believers
        in Laodicea and Hierapolis.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Luke, the beloved doctor, sends his greetings, and so does Demas. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Please give my greetings to our brothers and sisters[COMMENT[0]]
        at Laodicea, and to Nympha and the church that meets in her house.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: brothers.
    - title: 
      content: 'After you have read this letter, pass it on to the church at Laodicea
        so they can read it, too. And you should read the letter I wrote to them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And say to Archippus, \u201CBe sure to carry out the ministry the
        Lord gave you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\tHere is my greeting in my own handwriting\u2014Paul\n\t.\n\tRemember
        my chains.\n\tMay God\u2019s grace be with you."
      comments: []
